race.comment: SOOTY AND SWEEP (6) has been kept fresh since scoring over 1800m at Gundagai. Drops back to the mile and has been kept up to the mark with a trial placing here. Expect him to take plenty of stitching. JINGU EXPRESS (3) made it three straight last time when scoring comfortably over this trip at Wagga. Winning rider sticks. Has to be taken seriously. WATOTO (7) pressed forward from a wide draw last start over this track and trip before fading late into sixth. Knocking on the door and gets a good chance to break through on the quick back-up. KERMA ART (13) hasn't won for a long time but has peaks that measure up. Worth keeping safe with Boudvillain booked.
